    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/258.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to inform you that I
                    received a telegram last night from Sr. Joaquin Armendaiz, who is now at Alpine,
                    Texas, in which he states that the Constitutionalists at Monterey have demanded
                    40,000 pesos from him as a payment to avoid the confiscation of his property. It
                    is absolutely impossible for him to pay this sum and he asks me to appeal to you
                    for protection.</p>
                <p>Sr. Armendaiz has never taken any part in the politics of Mexico; he has already
                    suffered greatly in his interests at the hands of the Constitutionalists, and if
                    this last demand is enforced, it means financial ruin to him.</p>
                <p>I beg you therefore to interpose your good offices on his behalf, and to make the
                    necessary representations to the Constitutionalists, in order to prevent the
                    confiscation of the property of my compatriot.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
